---
import PolicyLayout from '../layouts/PolicyLayout.astro';
---
<PolicyLayout title="Privacy Notice">
  <p><em>Last updated: 5 June 2026</em></p>

  <p>This privacy notice explains how Science Works Limited uses your personal information. It tells you what we collect, why, and what rights you have.</p>

  <p>Science Works Limited is a company limited by guarantee registered in England and Wales, company number 17034971. Our registered office is 167–169 Great Portland Street, London, W1W 5PF.</p>

  <p>If you have a question about how we use your personal information, email <a href="mailto:contact@science.works">contact@science.works</a></p>

  <h2>What we collect and why</h2>

  <h3>When you contact us</h3>
  <p>If you email us or use a contact form on our website, we collect your name and email address. We use this to reply to you.</p>
  <p>We keep this information for as long as we need to deal with your enquiry, and delete it when it is no longer needed.</p>
  <p>Our legal basis for this is legitimate interests: responding to people who contact us.</p>

  <h3>When you sign up for updates</h3>
  <p>If you sign up to hear from us, we collect your email address. We use this to send you updates about our work.</p>
  <p>We keep your email address for as long as you are subscribed. If you unsubscribe, we delete it within 10 working days.</p>
  <p>Our legal basis for this is consent: you actively chose to sign up.</p>
  <p>We use Brevo to manage our mailing list. If you sign up for updates, your email address and any related mailing-list preferences will be stored by Brevo on our behalf.</p>
  <p>Brevo stores this data within the European Union, including in France, Germany and Belgium. Transfers of personal data from the UK to these countries are permitted under UK data protection law as they are covered by UK adequacy arrangements.</p>
  <p>You can unsubscribe at any time by using the unsubscribe link in our emails.</p>

  <h3>Who we share your information with</h3>
  <p>We do not sell your personal information to anyone.</p>

  <h2>Your rights</h2>
  <p>Under data protection law, you have the right to:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>ask for a copy of the personal information we hold about you</li>
    <li>ask us to correct information that is wrong</li>
    <li>ask us to delete your personal information</li>
    <li>ask us to stop using your personal information in certain circumstances</li>
    <li>ask for your personal information in a format you can take to another provider</li>
    <li>withdraw your consent at any time, where we rely on consent</li>
  </ul>
  <p>To make any of these requests, email <a href="mailto:info@science.works">info@science.works</a></p>

  <h2>Complaints</h2>
  <p>If you are unhappy with how we have handled your personal information, you have the right to complain to the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO).</p>
  <p>You can find out how to do this at <a href="https://ico.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">ico.org.uk</a> or call 0303 123 1113.</p>

  <h2>Changes to this notice</h2>
  <p>We may update this privacy notice from time to time. We will publish any changes on this page.</p>
</PolicyLayout>
